<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Musicians playing for Opera Pacific will receive a 19% increase in wages and 
benefits, the company announced Monday.According to a contract with the Orange 
County Musicians Union, Local 7, of the American Federation of Musicians, the 
increase will be spread over the next four years. The new starting rates range 
from $128.50 to $192.75 per performance and from $102.76 to $154.14 per 
rehearsal. The contract, signed in August, runs from Sept. 1, 1994, through 
Aug. 31, 1998. It also gives the Irvine-based company permission to broadcast 
one production per season over radio in Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
 Compiled by Kathy Stickel 
</P>
</TEXT>
