<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY EARNINGS: FIRM CUTS WORKERS' COMP CLAIMS BY ABOUT HALF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Martin V. Smith & Associates development firm has reduced its employees' 
work-related injuries and workers' compensation claims for the past year by 
about 50%, an insurance firm reports. 
</P>
<P>
 Tolman & Wiker Insurance, based in Ventura, said the Smith concern, developer 
of Oxnard's Financial Plaza, has been refunded nearly 50% of its workers' 
compensation premiums through a program offered by Fremont Compensation 
Insurance Co. 
</P>
<P>
 "Their diligence in promoting safe working practices among their employees has 
done more than reduce on-the-job injuries," Greg Anderson, a Tolman & Wiker 
partner, said of Smith & Associates. "It also has helped reduce the severity of 
the injuries that occur." 
</P>
<P>
 Dan Weigel, Smith's safety director, invites employees' own health-care 
practitioners to conduct safety programs at work sites. The company has 1,000 
workers throughout Ventura County. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a very effective means of getting the employees to discuss their 
concerns," Weigel said. He said he conducts safety programs at work sites 
rather than at company headquarters because employees are more apt to discuss 
such matters in a familiar environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
