<TEXT>
<P>
 Priscilla McDaniel, director of education/marketing for Consumer Credit 
Counseling Service of the Tri-Counties, a nonprofit credit-counseling agency in 
Ventura, was elected vice chairman and named chairman of next summer's session, 
Business Week '95. 
</P>
<P>
 Named to the executive board were Carolyn Leavens of Leavens Ranches, Ed Lyon 
of Gaviota Maintenance, Ron Baker of Southern California Edison, Armand Yates, 
Ed McDaniel of Professional Management Services, Evie Bystrom-Herrera, Rosalie 
Gehres of Great Western Bank and Ken Gerhardt, foundation founder. 
</P>
<P>
 Other trustees elected were Norm Lueck, Clint Crowell, James Hardy, Tom 
Umenhofer and Gig Wishon. 
</P>
