<HEADLINE>
<P>
'DUELING PROPHETS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Normally, I overcome inertia and write to The Times only when an article has 
left me outraged.However, Times staff writer Susan Moffat has inspired me to 
write and offer my congratulations for her "Dueling Prophets of Next L.A." 
(Nov. 19). Her warm, finely-crafted, ironic and poignant piece on Mike Davis 
and Kevin Starr is one of the best things I have ever seen in The Times. She 
had me intrigued with, charmed by, laughing at and then cheering these two 
brilliant characters. 
</P>
<P>
 The images the Moffat creates in her description of the odd couple touring Los 
Angeles are wonderful. I thought I was watching a Frank Capra movie. Thanks for 
taking me along. 
</P>
<P>
 ROGER McGRATH 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
