<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; VFW POST WILL MEET FOR FIRST TIME 
FRIDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A new Veterans of Foreign Wars post has been formed in the city. Eligible 
veterans joining before Feb. 1, 1995, will become charter members of Post 
11548. 
</P>
<P>
 Starting with more than 80 veterans, members will meet at 7:30 p.m. on the 
first and third Fridays of each month, beginning Friday, in Room B-6 at the 
Civic Center, 2000 Main St. 
</P>
<P>
 Elected to serve as officers of the new post are Gary Shiffman, commander; 
Robert E. Smith, senior vice commander; Robert Deets Jr., vice commander; Alex 
P. Pavlin, quartermaster; Earl B. Drabant, advocate; Cecil W. Birnbaum, 
chaplain; Sam A. Mazzara, surgeon; and Stanley J. Cohen, Gary C. Bean and 
Raymond J. Calderman, trustees. All live in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 People interested in becoming members may call Shiffman at (714) 846-8696, or 
Walter Davis, post adviser, (714) 997-7119. DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
