<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; CHILDREN'S HOLIDAY FESTIVAL SET FOR DEC. 
10 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A free holiday festival for children will be held Dec. 10 at the Market on the 
Lake shopping center. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will include free train rides, photos with Santa Claus, and ornament 
and card making. 
</P>
<P>
 Several community schools and church groups will perform a selection of 
holiday music during the event. Participating will be choirs from the Mission 
Hills Christian Center, Ocean Hills Community Church, Mission Viejo Church of 
Christ and Morning Star Christian Fellowship. 
</P>
<P>
 Students from Del Cerro Elementary School, Del Lago Elementary School, Hankey 
Elementary School and Arroyo Vista Elementary School also are scheduled to 
perform. 
</P>
<P>
 The festival will take place from 10 a.m. to 3 p.m. at the shopping center, on 
Marguerite Parkway at Vista del Lago. For more information, call (714) 
582-0204.FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
