CRAFTS FAIR OFFERS HOLIDAY GIFT ITEMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An arts and crafts fair featuring holiday gifts began Monday at the Student 
Center patio of Golden West College and will continue through Friday.The sale 
hours are 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 "The annual craft fair is designed to raise money to benefit economically 
disadvantaged Golden West College students, enabling them and their families to 
have a brighter Christmas," said the college's student activities director, 
Valerie Venegas. 
</P>
<P>
 Christmas ornaments, plush toy animals and gourmet foods are among items on 
sale at the fair. There is no admission charge. 
