<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: ATLANTA INVESTOR BUYS 6% SHARE IN MICROPOLIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Atlanta investor has acquired a 6% stake in Micropolis Corp., a 
Chatsworth-based disk drive manufacturer, by purchasing 910,000 common shares 
for $6.7 million, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
 The investor, Richard C. Perry, president of Perry & Co., an Atlanta insurance 
company, bought the Micropolis shares for investment, according to documents 
filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission. 
</P>
<P>
 Perry already held a smaller stake in Micropolis, but added to it by 
purchasing 505,000 shares in the open market between Sept. 22 and Nov. 21 for 
$6.18 to $9.17 per share, according to SEC documents. Those purchases boosted 
his stake to 6% of the company. 
</P>
<P>
 Micropolis reported a loss of $10.9 million on sales of $70.3 million in the 
third quarter that ended Sept. 30. 
</P>
