<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: ACCESS HEALTHNET PROFIT SURGES TO $426,048 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Access Healthnet Inc., a Westlake Village provider of communication systems 
that connect doctors, hospitals and labs, reported a sharp increase in earnings 
in its fiscal second quarter that ended Sept. 30. 
</P>
<P>
 Earnings surged to $426,048 in the quarter, up from $66,796 in the same 
quarter a year earlier.Revenues in the latest quarter were $2.97 million 
compared to $541,162 in the same quarter of 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 For the six-month period, Access posted earnings of $788,020 on sales of $5.25 
million, compared to a profit of $125,026 on sales of $1.68 million a year 
earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 Keith Berman, chief executive of Access Healthnet, said contracts with some of 
the country's largest laboratory and hospital management companies "have 
provided us with a steady stream of recurring revenues and, more importantly, 
have given our products national exposure." 
</P>
