<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: ACCOUNTANT OFFERS ADVICE ON PAPERWORK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John (Jack) Jacobs, president of Jacobs & Jacobs, an accounting firm that 
operates in Ventura County, raises a question: How would business people keep 
up with today's mounting paperwork requirements without computers? 
</P>
<P>
 "I guess the computers make it possible to survive," he said."Then again, 
maybe we wouldn't have to make so many reports if we didn't have the machines 
to do them on." 
</P>
<P>
 His advice to business people who feel that they're overburdened by the 
constant need to record tax, environmental and employee information: "Look past 
the problem. Concentrate on your opportunities." 
</P>
<P>
 Jacobs, 47, and two partners operate a firm that was founded in Ojai 50 years 
ago by Jacobs' father, Jodfrey. An uncle, Anzac Jacobs, later joined the 
company. In addition to Ojai, Jacobs & Jacobs has offices in Simi Valley and 
Thousand Oaks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
