<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jerry Hick; Jim Washburn, ; Rene Lynch 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 TWO HAPPY, ONE SAD: If you have heard those horror stories about how tough it 
is to pass the state bar exam, here's an upbeat note: In the July California 
bar exam, 63% passed -- the highest percentage in the last 32 years! Santa Ana 
appellate court Justice Edward J. Wallin suggests: "Law students are getting 
brighter -- and better prepared.". . . He gets to know them well too. Wallin 
has spoken before 21 of the last 22 groups in Orange County to be sworn in as 
lawyers. He sees them again Dec. 13 at the Hyatt Regency Alicante in Garden 
Grove. 
</P>
<P>
 ALUM ALERT: There's good reason why the Art Institute of Southern California 
doesn't have an alumni association. The small Laguna Beach college for arts or 
graphic design has been giving degrees only since 1986. But now some ambitious 
alumni trying to organize a group have a dinner meeting planned on campus 
Wednesday night. . . . Says institute president John Lottes: "We'd like to 
build a network to recommend students to us and also help us with job 
placement." 
</P>
<P>
 WIDER MESSAGE: Close friends of Rusty Kennedy, executive director of the 
Orange County Human Relations Commission, know it's more than just a job to 
him. Kennedy passionately believes in its causes, defusing racial tensions and 
fighting hate crimes. Now Kennedy has a chance to spread the word even wider. . 
. . He's the new president of the state Assn. of Human Rights Organizations. 
Says Kennedy: "We are being torn apart at the seams by fears. . . . We must 
pull together." 
</P>
<P>
 LITTLE IS BETTER? Canadian singer and harpist Loreena McKennitt has gone from 
street-corner gigs to top-selling albums and a soundtrack slot in Disney's No. 
1 film "The Santa Clause." But she worries about getting too big: "It's harder 
to get that connection from inside you to the audience in a larger hall. I 
don't see my music working in a hall bigger than 2,500 seats." . . . 
Fortunately, her performance tonight is at the Irvine Barclay Theatre (F1). 
It's 756 seats. 
</P>
