<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: STUDIO CITY; OPEN HOUSE AT SHOPS RINGS IN HOLIDAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It's beginning to look a lot like Christmas in Studio City. 
</P>
<P>
 Holiday lights are being strung across storefronts to prepare for a community 
open house sponsored by the Studio City Chamber of Commerce Dec. 9. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Claus will make an appearance in the courtyard of the Bank of America at 
4 p.m., and some merchants will serve hot cider in their stores. Other shop 
owners will conduct prize drawings, according to chamber President Jave 
McWilliams. Schools, churches and clubs have been invited to send groups to 
sing carols. Volunteer singers may call the chamber at (818) 769-3213 for more 
information. KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
