<HEADLINE>
<P>
LATE SURGE TAKES FRESNO STATE PAST PEPPERDINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Darnell McCulloch scored 23 points and Dominick Young made two baskets in the 
final minute to lead Fresno State to a 79-76 non-conference victory over 
Pepperdine on Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Young scored both of his baskets after making steals to spark an eight-point 
run for Fresno State (1-0). Young's first basket tied the game at 72. After 
Anthony Pelle's dunk, Young stole an inbounds pass and scored to give the 
Bulldogs a four-point lead over the Waves (1-1) with 25 seconds to play. 
</P>
</TEXT>
