<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: ANGELES NATIONAL 
FOREST; 2 KILLED IN CRASH AS CAR GOES OFF MOUNTAIN ROAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A car careened off the Angeles Crest Highway and tumbled at least 200 feet 
down a mountainside today, killing at least two of five adults reportedly in 
the vehicle.  
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred about 2:20 p.m. near mile marker 42 on the mountain road 
in the Angeles National Forest, said county Fire Inspector Dan Ertel. 
</P>
<P>
 The injured were taken to hospitals by sheriff's helicopters. 
</P>
