<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; VACANT SCHOOL TO BE LEASED TO CHURCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Westminster School District will lease the vacant Franklin Elementary 
School to the Christian Reformed Church of Orange County, a district 
spokeswoman has announced. 
</P>
<P>
 Church officials' plans call for using the site, at 14422 Hammon Lane, for 
church services, Sunday school, meetings and other activities. Proceeds from 
the lease will be used to fund improvements districtwide, district spokeswoman 
Audrey Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
 The nine-acre campus was closed in June because of changing enrollment 
patterns. Under the terms of the lease, which are still being worked out, the 
church will pay the district about $100,000. Neighborhood children will 
continue to have full access to the play fields, Brown said. JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
