COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; TASK FORCE TO REVIEW THE PUBLIC COMMENTS 
ABOUT TENNIS CENTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City officials have called a special meeting for Wednesday to get public 
comment on how to operate the Marguerite and Felipe tennis centers. 
</P>
<P>
 A tennis task force and city staff will review the results of a recent 
questionnaire and seek comment on running the 13 lighted tennis courts.The 
meeting will be at 6:30 p.m. at the Montanoso Recreation Center, 25800 
Montanoso Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 "We want to provide an opportunity for members of the public who are 
interested in tennis to comment on what to do with the centers," said Kelly 
Doyle, director of the city recreation department. "We're inviting them as 
users to formulate some ideas and share them with us." 
</P>
<P>
 The questionnaire was sent to about 2,500 users of the tennis courts and the 
four city recreation centers. City staff is tabulating the results and will 
announce them at the Wednesday meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 In a related development, the city has received four proposals from firms that 
want to run the two tennis centers. 
</P>
<P>
 The firm selected would contract with the city to operate the tennis centers, 
similar to the deal that currently allows Sports Leisure Group to run the city 
recreation centers. Sports Leisure Group is one of the four companies that 
submitted proposals. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 470-3061. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
