<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHURCH YOUTH LEADER RECEIVES 3-YEAR SENTENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RENE LYNCH, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A former youth group leader at a local church was sentenced Monday to three 
years in prison for molesting four boys. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Webb Blinkhorn, 29, had pleaded guilty to 18 felony counts of 
molestation involving four youths age 12 to 15.The molestations took place at 
Blinkhorn's home in Placentia between January, 1991, and July, 1993, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Attorneys could not be reached for comment after the sentencing late Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 At the time of the molestations, Blinkhorn was a volunteer with the First 
Evangelical Free Church of Fullerton, where he worked for about four years. He 
spent up to eight hours a week with a group of about 10 boys, helping them with 
Bible study and leading a Sunday morning youth program. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said none of the victims, one from Anaheim and three from 
Fullerton, were in Blinkhorn's study group. Blinkhorn was arrested in March 
after a monthlong investigation by the Placentia Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Blinkhorn also confessed to church elders after a youth on a retreat 
complained to another counselor of the alleged acts. Blinkhorn, who underwent a 
church screening process before he was allowed to volunteer, was then removed 
from his job. 
</P>
<P>
 The church has encouraged Blinkhorn's victims to seek counseling. 
</P>
