<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; KIDNAP, RAPE SUSPECT IS CLEARED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Prosecutors refused to file charges Monday against a Santa Clarita man who was 
arrested last week on suspicion of kidnap and rape after he provided 
investigators with a valid alibi. 
</P>
<P>
 Steven Bloomer, 40, was arrested Nov. 21 after an unidentified prostitute told 
police that Bloomer had taken her to a Santa Clarita location where she watched 
him molest a 5-year-old girl.The prostitute had also told police that Bloomer 
attacked her as well. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputy Dist. Atty. Dan Damon said Monday investigators had determined that the 
little girl was with her grandmother at the time of the alleged molestation. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was factually impossible," Damon said. "Her story didn't hold up." 
</P>
<P>
 Bloomer, who described the experience as the worst of his life, said he was 
grateful to the sheriff's investigator who checked out his story and cleared 
him of wrongdoing. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was very humiliating and very shaming," Bloomer said. "There were 
accusations that just didn't coincide with what really happened, but I had 
evidence showing where I was and what had really happened." 
</P>
</TEXT>
