<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALGERIA REPORTS KILLING 49 ISLAMIC GUERRILLAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Security forces said Monday that they killed 49 Islamic guerrillas during the 
weekend, boosting the death toll for what already was the deadliest month of 
the three-year insurgency. 
</P>
<P>
 The unofficial tally for November stands at 391 guerrillas and an unknown 
number of government troops killed. More than 11,000 people have been killed 
since the start of the guerrilla war in January, 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
