<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRE KILLS 233 IN CHINA DANCE HALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A huge fire swept through a crowded dance hall in northeastern China, killing 
233 people and injuring 16, local officials said today.  
</P>
<P>
 The fire occurred Sunday afternoon in the dance hall in the town of Fuxin in 
Liaoning province, an official of the Liaoning provincial Fire Prevention 
Department said by telephone from the province's capital, Shenyang. 
</P>
<P>
 Local news reports said five of the 16 injured were seriously burned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
