enforce a ban on a statewide general strike Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The strikers were demanding the resignation of the Maharashtra state 
government for allowing police to charge a tribal demonstration Nov. 23, 
allegedly causing protesters to stampede. 
</P>
<P>
 Adivasis, members of India's many small tribes fighting for affirmative action 
programs, were demanding some of the guaranteed jobs and school slots other 
ethnic groups receive. 
</P>
<P>
 A truck driver died and three people were injured in Bombay, the state's 
largest city, when protesters stoned a train, a bus and trucks, the Press Trust 
of India news agency said. 
</P>
<P>
 Burning tires thrown by demonstrators also set fire to a train, two cars and a 
rickshaw there, but firefighters quickly put out the blazes. 
</P>
<P>
 In Nagpur, the state's winter capital, opposition leaders and about 60 
supporters were detained when they tried to prevent a state official from 
entering the legislature. 
</P>
<P>
 Elsewhere in the city, about 40 people were arrested trying to stone buses or 
block legislators from leaving their hotel. No injuries were reported. 
</P>
