 Bakker, 54, was convicted in 1989 after he and his then-wife, Tammy Faye, 
allegedly spent millions of dollars bilked from members of the now-defunct 
Praise the Lord club. They bought a host of extravagances, including homes and 
an air-conditioned dog house. 
