<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michelle Bray 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach, Junior 
</P>
<P>
 Tennis/Singles 
</P>
<P>
 Earlier this season, Bray had an incredible streak for the Artists, winning 
101 consecutive games . The streak spanned seven matches before being stopped 
in a victory over Marina in the first round of the Division II playoffs.Bray 
completed her season with a 6-0, 6-0, 6-1 performance in the top-ranked 
Artists' 12-6 victory over Los Alamitos in the title match Tuesday. "Michelle 
is really hard to beat when she is on," Laguna Beach Coach Bob Walton said. 
"She's never going to give you any points." Bray and fellow juniors Amanda 
Hastings-Phillips and Lindsay Weiss won all nine singles sets as Laguna Beach 
(23-1) won its third consecutive title. Cross-country 
</P>
<P>
 Heather Garritson 
</P>
<P>
 * Buena Park, freshman. Won the State Division III race, running 3.1 miles in 
18 minutes 1 second, the second-fastest time of the day. 
</P>
<P>
 Courtney Pugmire 
</P>
<P>
 * Esperanza, senior. Finished second in the Division I race in 18:08, the 
second-fastest time for an Orange County runner. Volleyball 
</P>
<P>
 Mindi Adam 
</P>
<P>
 * Huntington Beach, senior. Had 54 assists in the Oilers' four-game victory 
over Edison in the Southern California Regional Division II playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 Courtney Owens 
</P>
<P>
 Jenny Roberts 
</P>
<P>
 * Calvary Chapel. Each had 12 kills in the Eagles' 15-2, 15-7, 15-7 victory 
over Sierra Madre Maranatha in the Southern California Regional Division IV 
playoffs. 
</P>
