<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: AUTOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ford Returning to South Africa: Six years after divesting because of 
apartheid, Ford Motor Co. announced that it would buy back some of the 
operation it left behind and formally re-enter South Africa. The size of the 
investment was not disclosed, but Ford promised to inject cash, new equipment 
and products into South African Motor Corp. Ltd., known as Samcor, which 
assembles Ford, Mazda and Mitsubishi vehicles. The agreement signed by 
officials from Ford and Anglo American Industrial Corp. Ltd., Samcor's holding 
company, gives each a 45% stake in Samcor, with the Samcor Employees Trust 
holding 10%. 
</P>
</TEXT>
