<TEXT>
<P>
 403,000 Cadillacs Recalled: General Motors Corp. is recalling Cadillac De 
Villes manufactured between 1991 and 1993 to replace a defective rubber oil 
hose that could create a fire risk.The company said the hose could separate 
from a connector and spill oil in the engine compartment. GM said it had 
reports of 27 fires related to the defect but no injuries. It said recall 
notices would be sent to owners over the next six to eight weeks. 
</P>
