BRIEFLY: AEROSPACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 McDonnell Douglas, Boeing to Form Partnership: The two firms will announce 
today they are forming a partnership to bid for a NASA contract to develop a 
new space launch vehicle that would reach orbit with a single stage, industry 
sources said. McDonnell's Aerospace unit in Huntington Beach will team with 
Boeing's Defense & Space Group to submit a bid for the X-33 program, an 
experimental launch system sponsored by the National Aeronautics and Space 
Administration. NASA plans to issue several initial contracts to design such a 
vehicle over a 13-month period and then select a single team in 1996 to being 
construction. 
</P>
