<TEXT>
<P>
 Weekend Holiday Sales Up: Sales at shopping centers nationwide rose 4.5% over 
the three-day post-Thanksgiving weekend compared to the same period a year ago, 
according to a report based on a survey of 85 malls.The New York-based 
International Council of Shopping Centers said the survey was based on sales 
receipts of about 5,000 specialty retail stores at the nation's largest 
shopping centers on Friday, Saturday and Sunday. Shopping center department 
stores were not included in the study. Meanwhile, Visa USA said it recorded 
$1.9 billion in sales authorizations on Friday and Saturday, a 24.4% increase 
and a record for that two-day post-Thanksgiving period. 
