<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: AEROSPACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AlliedSignal to Cut 1,000 Jobs: The firm said it will eliminate the jobs over 
the next eight months at the former Textron Lycoming engine plant in Stratford, 
Conn.AlliedSignal last month completed the purchase of Textron Lycoming, the 
turbine engine division of Providence, R.I.-based Textron Inc. It said the 
acquisition would result in job cuts as it combined the business with its 
Phoenix-based engines unit. The job cuts, due to begin in December, will leave 
about 1,200 employees at Stratford. The Lycoming Turbine Engine Division makes 
engines for airliners, helicopters, military tanks and marine applications. 
</P>
</TEXT>
