<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: OTHER NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Biotech Firm Strikes Deal With Bayer: Arris Pharmaceutical Corp. said Bayer AG 
will invest up to $70 million as part of an agreement to jointly develop 
anti-inflammatory drugs. Under the agreement, Arris, a South San Francisco 
biotechnology company, will receive royalties and Bayer, a Germany-based drug 
company, will receive worldwide manufacturing and marketing rights on any drugs 
that they develop together. Arris will receive an initial payment and 
additional funds as it reaches certain milestones. 
</P>
</TEXT>
