<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: COMPANY TOWN; MUSICAL CHAIRS AT TIME WARNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former top music industry lawyer Ina Meibach has become the latest senior Time 
Warner music executive to shift jobs as part of the continuing overhaul of the 
operation's executive ranks. 
</P>
<P>
 The longtime music industry lawyer, whose clients have included U2, was named 
executive vice president of Warner Music-U.S., where she will work under newly 
named Chairman Doug Morris and President Mel Lewinter. 
</P>
<P>
 Earlier this year, Meibach left her law practice at Meibach Epstein & Regis to 
join Time Warner's Atlantic Group unit, where she has been executive vice 
president and general counsel. 
</P>
<P>
 * Rene Vance was named marketing manager and Yvonne Fernandes was named 
affiliate relations manager for Turner Broadcasting System's World Championship 
Wrestling. 
</P>
<P>
 * Alan Citron, Times assistant business editor in charge of entertainment 
coverage, is joining Ticketmaster in the newly created post of vice president, 
publications and media ventures. 
</P>
<P>
 * PolyGram Music Publishing named John Baldi vice president of A&R. He 
previously was creative director. 
</P>
<P>
 * Prime Ticket Network named Patrick McClenahan vice president of programming 
and Bob Gold vice president of marketing and communications. 
</P>
<P>
 * Universal Pictures promoted Monika Skerbeles to vice president, creative and 
story department. 
</P>
<P>
 * Kevin McCormick signed a two-year producing and consulting deal with 20th 
Century Fox's new untitled movie division headed by Laura Ziskin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
